    "questionText": "<p>The remainder, when $7^{103}$ is divided by 23, is equal to:</p>",
    "options": [
      "<p>9</p>",
      "<p>6</p>",
      "<p>14</p>",
      "<p>17</p>"
    ],
    "correctOption": 2,
    "correctAnswer": null,
    "questionType": "MCQ",
    "marks": 4,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Mathematics",
    "topic": "divisibility-concept-and-remainder-concept",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n& 7^{103}=7\\left(7^{102}\\right)=7(343)^{34}=7(345-2)^{34} \\\\\n& 7^{103}=23 \\mathrm{~K}_1+7.2^{34} \\\\\n& \\text { Now } 7.2^{34}=7 \\cdot 2^2 \\cdot 2^{32} \\\\\n& =28 \\cdot(256)^4 \\\\\n& =28(253+3)^4 \\\\\n& \\therefore 28 \\times 81 \\Rightarrow(23+5)(69+12) \\\\\n& 23 \\mathrm{~K}_2+60 \\\\\n& \\therefore \\text { Remainder }=14\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>",
    "section": "A",
    "type": "SCQ"
  },
