    "id": "1lgvpgm7l",
    "questionNumber": 64,
    "questionText": "<p>Let the number $$(22)^{2022}+(2022)^{22}$$ leave the remainder $$\\alpha$$ when divided by 3 and $$\\beta$$ when divided by 7. Then $$\\left(\\alpha^{2}+\\beta^{2}\\right)$$ is equal to :</p>",
    "options": [
      "13",
      "10",
      "20",
      "5"
    ],
    "correctOption": 3,
    "correctAnswer": null,
    "questionType": "MCQ",
    "marks": 4,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Mathematics",
    "topic": "divisibility-concept-and-remainder-concept",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "We have, $(22)^{2022}+(2022)^{22}$\n<br/><br/>As 2022 is completely divisible by 3\n<br/><br/>So, $(2022)^{22}$ is also divisible by 3\n<br/><br/>$(22)^{2022}=(21+1)^{2022}=(3 \\times 7+1)^{2022}=7 m+1$\n<br/><br/>$\\Rightarrow(22)^{2022}$ leave a remainder 1 , when divisible by 3 .\n<br/><br/>$\\therefore(22)^{2022}+(2022)^{22}$ leave a remainder when divisible by 3\n<br/><br/>$\\therefore \\alpha=1$\n<br/><br/>$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n(22)^{2022}+(2022)^{22} & =(21+1)^{2022}+(2023-1)^{22} \\\\\\\\\n& =7 K+1+7 \\mu+1=7(K+\\mu)+2\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n<br/><br/>$\\Rightarrow(22)^{2022}+(2022)^{22}$ leave a remainder 2 when divisible by 7\n<br/><br/>$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\therefore  \\beta=2 \\\\\\\\\n& \\text { Hence, }  \\alpha^2+\\beta^2=1^2+2^2=5\n\\end{aligned}\n$$",
    "section": "A",
    "type": "SCQ"
  },
