    "solution": "<p>Given,</p>\n<p>$$1 + 3 + {3^2} + {3^3} + \\,\\,.....\\,\\, + \\,\\,{3^{2021}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {3^0} + {3^1} + {3^2} + {3^3} + \\,\\,....\\,\\, + \\,\\,{3^{2021}}$$</p>\n<p>This is a G.P with common ratio = 3</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Sum $$ = {{1({3^{2022}} - 1)} \\over {3 - 1}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{{3^{2022}} - 1} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{{{({3^2})}^{2011}} - 1} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{{{(10 - 1)}^{1011}} - 1} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{\\left[ {{}^{1011}{C_0}\\,.\\,{{10}^{1011}} - {}^{1011}{C_1}\\,.\\,{{10}^{1010}} + \\,\\,.....\\,\\, - \\,\\,{}^{1011}{C_{1009}}\\,.\\,{{(10)}^2} + {}^{1011}{C_{1010}}\\,.\\,10 - {}^{1011}{C_{1011}}} \\right] - 1} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{{{10}^2}\\left[ {{}^{1011}{C_0}\\,.\\,{{(10)}^{1009}} - {}^{1011}{C_1}\\,.\\,(1008) + \\,\\,.....\\,\\,{}^{1011}{C_{1009}}} \\right] + 10110 - 1 - 1} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{100k + 10110 - 2} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{100k + 10108} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 50k + 5054$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 50k + 50 \\times 101 + 4$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 50[k + 101] + 4$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 50k' + 4$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ By dividing 50 we get remainder as 4.</p>",
    "section": "B",
    "type": "NUMERICAL"
  },
  {
    "id": "1l5c0s15h",
    "questionNumber": 66,
    "questionText": "<p>The remainder when 3<sup>2022</sup> is divided by 5 is :</p>",
    "options": [
      "1",
      "2",
      "3",
      "4"
    ],
    "correctOption": 3,
    "correctAnswer": null,
    "questionType": "MCQ",
    "marks": 4,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Mathematics",
    "topic": "divisibility-concept-and-remainder-concept",
    "difficulty": "easy",
    "solution": "<p>$${3^{2022}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {({3^2})^{1011}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {(9)^{1011}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {(10 - 1)^{1011}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {}^{1011}{C_0}{(10)^{1011}} + \\,\\,.....\\,\\, + \\,\\,{}^{1011}{C_{1010}}\\,.\\,{(10)^1} - {}^{1011}{C_{1011}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 10\\left[ {{}^{1011}{C_0}{{(10)}^{1010}} + \\,\\,......\\,\\, + \\,\\,{}^{1011}{C_{1010}}} \\right] - 1$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 10\\,K - 1$$</p>\n<p>[As $$10\\left[ {{}^{1011}{C_0}\\,.\\,{{(10)}^{1010}} + \\,\\,......\\,\\, + \\,\\,{}^{1011}{C_{1010}}} \\right]$$ is multiple of 10]</p>\n<p>$$ = 10K + 5 - 5 - 1$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 10K - 5 + 5 - 1$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 5(2K - 1) + 4$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Unit digit = 4 when divided by 5.</p>",
    "section": "A",
    "type": "SCQ"
  },
  {
    "id": "1l6f0uwiw",
    "questionNumber": 63,
    "questionText": "<p>The remainder when $$(11)^{1011}+(1011)^{11}$$ is divided by 9 is</p>",
    "options": [
      "1",
      "4",
      "6",
      "8"
    ],
    "correctOption": 3,
    "correctAnswer": null,
    "questionType": "MCQ",
    "marks": 4,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Mathematics",
    "topic": "divisibility-concept-and-remainder-concept",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "<p>$${\\mathop{\\rm Re}\\nolimits} \\left( {{{{{(11)}^{1011}} + {{(1011)}^{11}}} \\over 9}} \\right) = {\\mathop{\\rm Re}\\nolimits} \\left( {{{{2^{1011}} + {3^{11}}} \\over 9}} \\right)$$</p>\n<p>For $${\\mathop{\\rm Re}\\nolimits} \\left( {{{{2^{1011}}} \\over 9}} \\right)$$</p>\n<p>$${2^{1011}} = {(9 - 1)^{337}} = {}^{337}{C_0}{9^{337}}{( - 1)^0} + {}^{337}{C_1}{9^{336}}{( - 1)^1} + {}^{337}{C_2}{9^{335}}{( - 1)^2} + \\,\\,.....\\,\\, + \\,\\,{}^{337}{C_{337}}{9^0}{( - 1)^{337}}$$</p>\n<p>So, remainder is 8 </p>\n<p>and $${\\mathop{\\rm Re}\\nolimits} \\left( {{{{3^{11}}} \\over 9}} \\right) = 0$$</p>\n<p>So, remainder is 8</p>",
    "section": "A",
    "type": "SCQ"
  },
  {
    "id": "1l5ai3wa2",
    "questionNumber": 62,
    "questionText": "<p>If $${1 \\over {2\\,.\\,{3^{10}}}} + {1 \\over {{2^2}\\,.\\,{3^9}}} + \\,\\,.....\\,\\, + \\,\\,{1 \\over {{2^{10}}\\,.\\,3}} = {K \\over {{2^{10}}\\,.\\,{3^{10}}}}$$, then the remainder when K is divided by 6 is :</p>",
    "options": [
      "1",
      "2",
      "3",
      "5"
    ],
    "correctOption": 3,
    "correctAnswer": null,
    "questionType": "MCQ",
    "marks": 4,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Mathematics",
    "topic": "divisibility-concept-and-remainder-concept",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "<p>$${1 \\over {2\\,.\\,{3^{10}}}} + {1 \\over {{2^2}\\,.\\,{3^9}}} + \\,\\,....\\,\\, + \\,\\,{1 \\over {{2^{10}}\\,.\\,3}} = {K \\over {{2^{10}}\\,.\\,{3^{10}}}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow {1 \\over {2\\,.\\,{3^{10}}}}\\left[ {{{{{\\left( {{3 \\over 2}} \\right)}^{10}} - 1} \\over {{3 \\over 2} - 1}}} \\right] = {K \\over {{2^{10}}\\,.\\,{3^{10}}}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{{3^{10}} - {2^{10}}} \\over {{2^{10}}\\,.\\,{3^{10}}}} = {K \\over {{2^{10}}\\,.\\,{3^{10}}}} \\Rightarrow K = {3^{10}} - {2^{10}}$$</p>\n<p>Now $$K = {(1 + 2)^{10}} - {2^{10}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {}^{10}{C_0} + {}^{10}{C_1}2 + {}^{10}{C_2}{2^3} + \\,\\,....\\,\\, + \\,\\,{}^{10}{C_{10}}{2^{10}} - {2^{10}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {}^{10}{C_0} + {}^{10}{C_1}2 + 6\\lambda  + {}^{10}{C_9}\\,.\\,{2^9}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 1 + 20 + 5120 + 6\\lambda $$</p>\n<p>$$ = 5136 + 6\\lambda  + 5$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 6\\mu  + 5$$</p>\n<p>$$\\lambda ,\\,\\mu  \\in N$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ remainder = 5</p>",
    "section": "A",
    "type": "SCQ"
  },
  {
    "id": "1l587i0nd",
    "questionNumber": 67,
    "questionText": "<p>The remainder when (2021)<sup>2023</sup> is divided by 7 is :</p>",
    "options": [
      "1",
