    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Mathematics",
    "topic": "divisibility-concept-and-remainder-concept",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "<p>$${(2021)^{2022}} + {(2022)^{2021}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {(7k - 2)^{2022}} + {(7{k_1} - 1)^{2021}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {\\left[ {{{(7k - 2)}^3}} \\right]^{674}} + {(7{k_1})^{2021}} - 2021{(7{k_1})^{2020}}\\, + \\,....\\, - 1$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {(7{k_2} - 1)^{674}} + (7m - 1)$$</p>\n<p>$$ = (7n + 1) + (7m - 1) = 7(m + n)$$ (multiple of 7)</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Remainder = 0</p>",
