    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Mathematics",
    "topic": "divisibility-concept-and-remainder-concept",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& 7^{2022}+3^{2022} \\\\\\\\\n& =\\left(7^2\\right)^{1011}+\\left(3^2\\right)^{1011} \\\\\\\\\n&=(50-1)^{1011}+(10-1)^{1011} \\\\\\\\\n&= (50^{1011}-1011.50^{1010}+\\ldots-1) \\\\\\\\\n& + (10^{1011}-1011.10^{1010}+\\ldots . .-1) \\\\\\\\\n&= 5 m-1+5 n-1=5(m+n)-2 \\\\\\\\\n&= 5(m+n)-5+3=5(m+n-1)+3 \\\\\\\\\n&= 5 k+3 \\\\\\\\\n& \\therefore \\text { Remainder }=3\n\\end{aligned}\n$$",
    "section": "A",
    "type": "SCQ"
  },
  {
